title: Money Market Reform Training Session
eventDescription:
Summary:
State Street's Jim Brewster hosts a training video which discusses overall approach and readiness to the Money Market Reform requirements.
Many clients are considering the use of intraday pricing points to address their Floating NAV liquidity needs and the trend seems to be moving towards one to four pricing points.
There has been several discussion around NAV error guidelines for a Floating NAV. The ICI believes it is highly unlikely SEC would address formally or informally � accordingly they think this is an issue that each fund/board should address on its own.
eventSpeakers: James Brewster; Lynne Winchester; Sheila McClorey

title: Money Market Reform Training
eventDescription: State Street's Jim Brewster hosts a training video which discusses overall approach and readiness to the Money Market Reform requirements. Many clients are considering the use of intraday pricing points to address their Floating NAV liquidity needs and the trend seems to be moving towards one to four pricing points.There has been several discussion around NAV error guidelines for a Floating NAV. The ICI believes it is highly unlikely SEC would address formally or informally accordingly they think this is an issue that each fund/board should address on its own.Valuation guidance is not limited to money funds, but applies to all funds. Essentially, a fund may continue to use amortized cost to value a debt security with a remaining maturity less than 60 days, so long as its board determines each time that amortized cost approximates the true value of such security. This implies that an analysis must be performed that confirms that the amortized cost is approximately the same as the market value.

title: T+2 Symposium
eventDescription:
The industry is planning to shorten the settlement cycle to trade date plus two business days, or T+2, in the U.S. by the end of Q3 2017. The instruments subject to the shortened settlement cycle include equities, corporate and municipal bonds, unit investment trusts, and financial instruments comprised of these products. 

 Discuss how firms can get ready for the move to T+2, including implementation timeline, milestones and dependencies, regulatory and rule changes for Legal, Compliance, Risk, Technology and Operations teams, vendor and service provider preparedness, and the framework for internal and industry-wide testing.
eventHost: Securities Industry and Financial Markets Association (SIFMA)
